<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 6:45PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Morgan,
southeastern Walton, northeastern Jasper and east central Newton
Counties through 715 PM EDT...
At 643 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Newborn, or 10 miles
west of Madison, moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind and heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Madison, Social Circle, Rutledge, Newborn, Mansfield, Ebenezer,
Farrar, Starrsville, Hard Labor Creek State Park, and Brick Store.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. Motorists should
slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
